The seven-man-woman that was the Junta de Gobierno was responsible for bringing one of the country’s own to the power. Its achievement was not only credited to the work of the board but also by the city and the country anticipating the joint effort. This was one of the moments when people really came together for a common purpose.

Besides this magnificent achievement, El Salvador’s been seen to believe that they need a true change in social order. As we can see in the last few years, the number of businesses and exports increased immensely. This is also due to the changing policy that has been implemented since then. The changes need traction and tracking the economy is one of the ways to get it working.

On the other hand, international aid keeps rolling in, which is a positive sign. Fast-talking’s and doing business in El Salvador are common and not many seem to mind the origins of the producer or the supplier as long as the business is profitable.

El Salvador is one of the fastest growing economies in Central America and Latin America. They have less developed programs from land management to water management. However, they remain successful in securing land rights for around 95% of the population with the help of the 1992 Land Law.
